### A15. Read Rate Limiting (HIGH — addresses ISSUE-22)

**Problem**: Dashboard endpoints run 6-10 aggregate queries per request. At 2000 users polling every 30s = 4000 req/min → DB saturation even with cache.

**Solution — Tiered Read Limits**:
```php
// AppServiceProvider.php
RateLimiter::for('api.read', function (Request $request) {
    $userId = $request->user()?->id ?? $request->ip();
    return Limit::perMinute(120)->by("read:{$userId}");
});

RateLimiter::for('api.read.heavy', function (Request $request) {
    $userId = $request->user()?->id ?? $request->ip();
    return Limit::perMinute(30)->by("heavy-read:{$userId}");
});

RateLimiter::for('api.search', function (Request $request) {
    $userId = $request->user()?->id ?? $request->ip();
    return Limit::perMinute(60)->by("search:{$userId}");
});
```

**Apply to routes**:
```php
// Heavy dashboard endpoints — 30 req/min
Route::middleware('throttle:api.read.heavy')->group(function () {
    Route::get('/fee-collection/dashboard', ...);
    Route::get('/revenue/overview', ...);
    Route::get('/leadership/dashboard', ...);
    Route::get('/leadership/risks', ...);
    Route::get('/customer-request-cases/dashboard/{role}', ...);
});

// Search endpoints — 60 req/min
Route::middleware('throttle:api.search')->group(function () {
    Route::get('/customer-request-cases/search', ...);
});

// Regular list GETs — 120 req/min
Route::middleware('throttle:api.read')->group(function () {
    // ... all other GET routes
});
```

