### A17. Frontend Resilience — Error Boundaries + Service Worker (MEDIUM — addresses ISSUE-23, ISSUE-24)

**1. Error Boundaries** (wrap every Suspense):
```typescript
// frontend/shared/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx
class AppErrorBoundary extends React.Component<Props, State> {
  state = { hasError: false, error: null };

  static getDerivedStateFromError(error: Error) {
    return { hasError: true, error };
  }

  componentDidCatch(error: Error, info: React.ErrorInfo) {
    Sentry.captureException(error, { extra: info }); // Forward to A10
  }

  render() {
    if (this.state.hasError) {
      return (
        <div className="p-8 text-center">
          <p className="text-red-600">Đã xảy ra lỗi. Vui lòng tải lại trang.</p>
          <button onClick={() => this.setState({ hasError: false })}>Thử lại</button>
        </div>
      );
    }
    return this.props.children;
  }
}

// Usage pattern — wrap every React.lazy Suspense:
<AppErrorBoundary>
  <Suspense fallback={<LoadingSpinner />}>
    <CustomerRequestHub />
  </Suspense>
</AppErrorBoundary>
```

**Placement rules**:
- Route-level: each page/hub gets its own boundary
- Modal-level: each lazy modal gets a boundary
- Root-level: `AppErrorBoundary` in AppWithRouter.tsx as catch-all

**2. Conservative Service Worker** (asset precache only):
```bash
cd frontend && npm install workbox-precaching workbox-routing -D
```

```typescript
// frontend/sw.ts — precache build assets only, NO API caching
import { precacheAndRoute, cleanupOutdatedCaches } from 'workbox-precaching';

precacheAndRoute(self.__WB_MANIFEST); // Vite injects asset manifest
cleanupOutdatedCaches();              // Clean old versions on deploy

// NO runtime API caching — TanStack Query handles that
// Kill switch: unregister SW via version flag
self.addEventListener('message', (event) => {
  if (event.data?.type === 'SKIP_WAITING') {
    self.skipWaiting();
  }
});
```

**Kill Switch**: Set `VITE_SW_ENABLED=false` → skip SW registration in `index.tsx`.
**Deploy Safety**: `cleanupOutdatedCaches()` + `skipWaiting()` ensures new deploy invalidates old SW cache.

